description: at csulb i am a university honors program student who is under engineering honors track 2. before graduating, i will complete my undergraduate thesis on a computer-science related topic.

i currently serve as vice president at acm, csulb. i've previously served as co-vice president and beachhacks organizer. within the past three years in acm, i've made positive and impactful contributions to the computer science community at csulb.
i am currently serving as the outreach lead for gdsc at csulb. i am responsible for creating and executing outreach strategies to increase the club's visibility and membership.
as a webmaster at aesb, i've rebuilt the legacy website from scratch using react, typescript, and material ui. i continue to maintain the website and the club's social media.
for the 2020-2021 academic year, i competed at the socal international collegiate programming contest (icpc) regionals.
as a stem advantage scholar, i am a part of a cohort of hundreds of csu low-income students who are committed to pursuing a career in stem.
